### Call Discovered Service with x402 Client (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/coinbase/x402/blob/main/docs/extensions/bazaar.mdx

This snippet shows how to use the x402 client in TypeScript to call a discovered service. It involves setting up an EVM account, registering it with the client, wrapping an Axios instance for payment, and making a request based on the service's input schema. Dependencies include '@x402/axios', '@x402/evm/exact/client', 'axios', and 'viem/accounts'.

```typescript
import { wrapAxiosWithPayment, x402Client } from "@x402/axios";
import { ExactEvmScheme } from "@x402/evm/exact/client";
import axios from "axios";
import { privateKeyToAccount } from "viem/accounts";

// Set up your payment account
const account = privateKeyToAccount("0xYourPrivateKey");
const client = new x402Client();
client.register("eip155:*", new ExactEvmScheme(account));

// Select a service from discovery
const selectedService = affordableServices[0];

// Create a payment-enabled client for that service
const api = wrapAxiosWithPayment(
  axios.create({ baseURL: selectedService.resource }),
  client
);

